CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 27, 1954, pg. 13 reads: "The Glamorous Cotillion - Scenes from the third annual debutante Cotillion given by Pittsburgh AKAs...center photos show part of the smartly gowned patrons who watched avidly as the beautiful pageant unfolded..."
TitMainTitle: Group of men, and women, including woman seated on left with legs crossed wearing light colored gown with dark halter top, dark gloves, and short veil, seated in Syria Mosque for Alpha Kappa Alpha's 1954 Cotillion
